1
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:45,962
вЂЄSPOOKY IN LOVE

2
00:01:39,098 --> 00:01:40,183
вЂЄCEO CHEON YEO-RI

3
00:01:47,315 --> 00:01:49,400
вЂЄEPISODE 2

4
00:01:52,654 --> 00:01:55,740
вЂЄWhy do you run away
вЂЄwhenever we meet, Ms. Cheon?

5
00:01:55,824 --> 00:01:58,618
вЂЄI wasn't running away. I was avoiding you.

6
00:01:58,701 --> 00:02:01,788
вЂЄWhy avoid me like I'm some kind of virus?

7
00:02:02,747 --> 00:02:04,124
вЂЄOkay, fine. So you avoided me.

8
00:02:04,207 --> 00:02:06,459
вЂЄWhy do that
вЂЄif you're not guilty of anything?

9
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:09,254
вЂЄPeople who aren't guilty
вЂЄcan avoid others if they want.

10
00:02:09,337 --> 00:02:11,297
вЂЄOh, so you ignore everyone to start with?

11
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:13,508
вЂЄTo be honest, I couldn't stand you.

12
00:02:14,425 --> 00:02:15,718
вЂЄYou left a terrible first impression.

13
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:17,679
вЂЄI'd say you're just as bad in that aspect.

14
00:02:21,850 --> 00:02:24,519
вЂЄSo what is it that you want to know?

15
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:27,647
вЂЄYou reported the body on Mt. Haewang,
вЂЄdidn't you?

16
00:02:29,107 --> 00:02:30,942
вЂЄYou caught the culprit and found the body.

17
00:02:31,025 --> 00:02:32,485
вЂЄDoes it matter who reported it?

18
00:02:32,569 --> 00:02:34,487
вЂЄThere could be more than one culprit,

19
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:37,407
вЂЄand it's too suspicious
вЂЄthat you knew where the body was.

20
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:38,491
вЂЄAre you saying

21
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:40,827
вЂЄthat I'm the accomplice?

22
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:43,079
вЂЄIf something feels off,
вЂЄisn't it best to cover all bases?

23
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:44,956
вЂЄDelusion must come
вЂЄwith being a prosecutor.

24
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:46,875
вЂЄLet's say I'm here to check facts.

25
00:02:48,168 --> 00:02:50,003
вЂЄHow did you know the body was there?

26
00:02:52,922 --> 00:02:54,883
вЂЄYou seem to have asked
вЂЄall you wanted to know.

27
00:02:57,302 --> 00:02:58,219
вЂЄPlease leave.

28
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:01,431
вЂЄWhat's the point of asking
вЂЄwhen you didn't answer a single one?

29
00:03:02,765 --> 00:03:04,058
вЂЄTell me just one thing.

30
00:03:04,642 --> 00:03:06,019
вЂЄHow did you know the body was there?

31
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:09,230
вЂЄI was told.

32
00:03:11,774 --> 00:03:12,817
вЂЄBy whom?

33
00:03:13,484 --> 00:03:15,486
вЂЄ-By a ghost.
вЂЄ-What?

34
00:03:15,570 --> 00:03:17,822
вЂЄAre you kidding me right now?

35
00:03:19,198 --> 00:03:20,909
вЂЄWhy ask if you won't believe me?

36
00:03:20,992 --> 00:03:23,161
вЂЄAre you a psychic medium or a shaman

37
00:03:23,244 --> 00:03:25,121
вЂЄ-for a ghost to tell you that?
вЂЄ-Ms. Cheon.

38
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:41,012
вЂЄDid I hit the nail on the head?

39
00:03:41,095 --> 00:03:42,513
вЂЄNow I feel bad for no reason.

40
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:45,558
вЂЄHey!

41
00:03:48,811 --> 00:03:50,813
вЂЄI can't believe I'm seeing this.

42
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:52,607
вЂЄWhat are you doing in a place like this?

43
00:03:52,690 --> 00:03:55,068
вЂЄI come to such places often,
вЂЄto enforce search warrants.

44
00:03:57,237 --> 00:03:59,614
вЂЄWhat do you think?
вЂЄTotally luxurious, right?

45
00:03:59,697 --> 00:04:02,533
вЂЄThe owner of this hotel
вЂЄis my future cousin-in-law.

46
00:04:02,617 --> 00:04:05,370
вЂЄWant me to pull some strings
вЂЄand get you a membership?

47
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:08,706
вЂЄYou really must have a thing for hotels.

48
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:11,668
вЂЄJang Eun-ju disappeared from a hotel too,
вЂЄdidn't she?

49
00:04:14,837 --> 00:04:16,547
вЂЄWhy would you bring her up?

50
00:04:18,174 --> 00:04:19,008
вЂЄJust you wait.

51
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:21,719
вЂЄI'll find Jang Eun-ju's body,

52
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:23,513
вЂЄno matter how well you hid it.

53
00:04:23,596 --> 00:04:25,473
вЂЄYou have quite the imagination.

54
00:04:27,058 --> 00:04:29,143
вЂЄNice jacket. Looks good on you.

55
00:04:35,441 --> 00:04:36,901
вЂЄGhosts tell you stuff?

56
00:04:36,985 --> 00:04:37,819
вЂЄLike what?

57
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:39,779
вЂЄIt's nothing.

58
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,281
вЂЄI was just joking.

59
00:04:41,364 --> 00:04:44,409
вЂЄShaman Baek's suppression ritual
вЂЄto stop you from seeing things.

60
00:04:44,492 --> 00:04:45,368
вЂЄDid it fail?

61
00:04:45,994 --> 00:04:46,995
вЂЄOf course not.

62
00:04:48,621 --> 00:04:50,373
вЂЄDon't you act rash.

63
00:04:51,457 --> 00:04:53,501
вЂЄThere are eyes and ears everywhere.

64
00:04:54,168 --> 00:04:57,463
вЂЄA strange rumor has been
вЂЄgoing around already.

65
00:04:58,089 --> 00:04:59,507
вЂЄWhat kind of rumor?

66
00:05:01,884 --> 00:05:03,011
вЂЄThat you were ordained as a shaman.

67
00:05:04,804 --> 00:05:07,807
вЂЄI assume it was your ex-fiancГ©'s family
вЂЄwho started it.

68
00:05:08,808 --> 00:05:11,185
вЂЄJust make sure
вЂЄyou don't get caught up in gossip.

69
00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:13,813
вЂЄI'll be careful.

70
00:05:15,648 --> 00:05:16,482
вЂЄOh, right.

71
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:20,611
вЂЄAbout the Competitiveness
вЂЄImprovement Strategy.

72
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:24,991
вЂЄI thought you'd suggest
вЂЄwe drive Reina forward with an upgrade,

73
00:05:25,658 --> 00:05:27,618
вЂЄjust as luxury brands
вЂЄhave their high-end tier.

74
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:30,872
вЂЄReina Seoul will stick to the strategy
вЂЄto upgrade and improve.

75
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:33,333
вЂЄThe same goes
вЂЄfor the Busan and Gyeongju branches.

76
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,794
вЂЄBut if we consider the brand as a whole,

77
00:05:36,878 --> 00:05:39,255
вЂЄwe need a strategic revamp
вЂЄto change our structure.

78
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:42,550
вЂЄIt's not a decision
вЂЄto make here and now,

79
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:44,761
вЂЄbut I thought of CL Raymond Hotel.

80
00:05:45,428 --> 00:05:47,722
вЂЄI find their brand strategy
вЂЄquite appealing.

81
00:05:48,306 --> 00:05:51,267
вЂЄWhen CL Group opened their first hotel,

82
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:56,064
вЂЄthey collaborated with Raymond,
вЂЄthe global hotel chain, to succeed.

83
00:05:57,315 --> 00:06:00,276
вЂЄIt's true that global hotel chains
вЂЄare entering not only Seoul,

84
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:02,570
вЂЄbut other larger cities as well.

85
00:06:03,488 --> 00:06:06,741
вЂЄStill, I'm against it.
вЂЄWhy bother paying a fee to use a name?

86
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:10,286
вЂЄThey opened last year
вЂЄand you know how much they grew.

87
00:06:10,369 --> 00:06:11,454
вЂЄIt's not a bad idea.

88
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:13,247
вЂЄGive it some thought.

89
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:19,170
вЂЄIt's me. Where about are you?

90
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:21,422
вЂЄWhere else?
вЂЄI'm on my way back to the office.

91
00:06:22,006 --> 00:06:23,341
вЂЄDidn't you take the day off?

92
00:06:23,424 --> 00:06:25,134
вЂЄWhy would I take the day off?

93
00:06:25,718 --> 00:06:28,638
вЂЄPeople like me don't have the time
вЂЄto take days off.

94
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:31,974
вЂЄI've reminded you so many times
вЂЄsince last month.

95
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:35,061
вЂЄYou must do a good deed today
вЂЄduring the Hour of the Monkey.

96
00:06:35,144 --> 00:06:38,231
вЂЄI'm not some high schooler
вЂЄcollecting good deed miles for university.

97
00:06:38,314 --> 00:06:41,150
вЂЄGood deeds only work out
вЂЄif they come from the heart.

98
00:06:41,651 --> 00:06:45,321
вЂЄWhat's the point in doing good
вЂЄon an auspicious day just to avoid evilвЂ¦

99
00:06:45,404 --> 00:06:47,073
<i>вЂЄMy goodness.</i>

100
00:06:47,156 --> 00:06:50,618
<i>вЂЄMy one and only grandson</i>
<i>вЂЄdoesn't listen to a word I say.</i>

101
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:52,870
вЂЄIf you think that little of me,

102
00:06:52,954 --> 00:06:55,289
вЂЄI don't see the point
вЂЄin living any longer.

103
00:06:55,373 --> 00:06:56,958
вЂЄI've outlived my welcome.

104
00:06:57,041 --> 00:07:00,044
вЂЄCome on, don't say that.
вЂЄYou're breaking your grandson's heart.

105
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:02,463
вЂЄI'm on my way, okay?

106
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:04,006
вЂЄI'll take the afternoon off.

107
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:22,775
вЂЄCareful, kids.

108
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,403
вЂЄYou said you wanted this last time.

109
00:07:25,486 --> 00:07:28,197
вЂЄ-Be careful, guys.
вЂЄ-It's mine!

110
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:30,616
вЂЄ-One, two, three, let's go!
вЂЄ-Let's go!

111
00:07:33,536 --> 00:07:34,620
вЂЄPass it forward.

112
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:35,830
вЂЄWe lost the ball!

113
00:07:42,545 --> 00:07:43,379
вЂЄOh, no.

114
00:07:48,676 --> 00:07:51,053
вЂЄ-No, don't lose it!
вЂЄ-Get it!

115
00:07:51,137 --> 00:07:52,972
вЂЄHey, no.

116
00:07:53,055 --> 00:07:54,390
вЂЄFoul! That's a foul!

117
00:07:58,936 --> 00:08:01,981
вЂЄ-You couldn't block that?
вЂЄ-He aimed too well.

118
00:08:02,064 --> 00:08:04,108
вЂЄ-No, it's just thatвЂ¦
вЂЄ-How did you miss it?

119
00:08:25,254 --> 00:08:27,298
вЂЄ-That is bad.
вЂЄ-Oh, no.

120
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:31,093
вЂЄWe replaced that window
вЂЄjust three days ago.

121
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:33,304
вЂЄThe director's away on business, right?

122
00:08:33,387 --> 00:08:34,388
вЂЄYes, that's true.

123
00:08:34,972 --> 00:08:35,806
вЂЄI'll destroy the evidence.

124
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:38,643
вЂЄThe director's office is locked
вЂЄand we don't have the key.

125
00:08:38,726 --> 00:08:39,977
вЂЄThere's always a way.

126
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:41,646
вЂЄA way?

127
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:01,832
вЂЄI found the ball!

128
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:20,351
<i>вЂЄPeople who stayed in the rooms near Jang's</i>
<i>вЂЄaround the time of her disappearance?</i>

129
00:09:20,434 --> 00:09:22,687
вЂЄYes, those who stayed in the rooms
вЂЄnext to, above, and below hers,

130
00:09:22,770 --> 00:09:25,481
вЂЄthe times they checked in and out,
вЂЄand their alibis for that period.

131
00:09:25,982 --> 00:09:26,857
вЂЄGot it.

132
00:09:28,192 --> 00:09:29,860
вЂЄOkay.

133
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:35,074
<i>вЂЄPark Seung-jae sunk thrilling shot</i>
<i>вЂЄafter shot at the championship</i>

134
00:09:35,157 --> 00:09:38,119
<i>вЂЄand is now top of the leaderboard</i>
<i>вЂЄin the third round.</i>

135
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:43,583
вЂЄWow, you ripped the green
вЂЄlike you were shredding a stage.

136
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:46,377
вЂЄThis is embarrassing. Let's just drink.

137
00:09:47,503 --> 00:09:49,422
вЂЄMr. Park. You're pretty cool.

138
00:09:50,923 --> 00:09:52,592
вЂЄThis is just between us,

139
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:55,094
вЂЄbut isn't that score a miracle
вЂЄcompared to your previous games?

140
00:09:57,430 --> 00:09:59,932
вЂЄI mean, data is science,

141
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:02,351
вЂЄbut what beats science is luck.

142
00:10:02,435 --> 00:10:04,186
вЂЄI guess I got a lucky break.

143
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:05,855
вЂЄ-That's it.
вЂЄ-Yeah, nice.

144
00:10:06,355 --> 00:10:07,523
вЂЄ-Mom.
вЂЄ-Yes?

145
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:10,067
вЂЄShould we ask Shaman Baek
вЂЄto write him a talisman

146
00:10:10,151 --> 00:10:12,361
вЂЄso his luck doesn't run out?

147
00:10:13,904 --> 00:10:14,739
вЂЄWellвЂ¦

148
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:17,742
вЂЄWhy not? They say ghosts control luck.

149
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:20,828
вЂЄShaman Baek is best at handling spirits,
вЂЄlike what he did for Yeo-ri.

150
00:10:20,911 --> 00:10:22,246
вЂЄHa-ri.

151
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:25,291
вЂЄWas Ms. Cheon ever possessed by a ghost?

152
00:10:25,374 --> 00:10:26,667
вЂЄGosh, no.

153
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:28,544
вЂЄShe wasn't possessed.

154
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:31,505
вЂЄShe's a ghost herself,
вЂЄthe type that drags others down.

155
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:33,382
вЂЄShe totally badmouthed you last time.

156
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:35,009
вЂЄMe? What did she say?

157
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:36,469
вЂЄWhat was it again?

158
00:10:37,261 --> 00:10:39,764
вЂЄThat you dumped your ex for my money
вЂЄand that you're a parasite.

159
00:10:39,847 --> 00:10:40,973
вЂЄHey, don't.

160
00:10:41,474 --> 00:10:43,517
вЂЄWhat? She did say that.

161
00:10:45,269 --> 00:10:46,896
вЂЄYou can't just barge in like that.

162
00:10:50,691 --> 00:10:51,525
вЂЄWhat do you want?

163
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:57,990
вЂЄMs. Cheon,
вЂЄI hear you've been talking reckless.

164
00:10:59,408 --> 00:11:02,036
вЂЄThat I'm a parasite who dumped my ex

165
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:03,704
вЂЄfor Ha-ri's money.

166
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:08,626
вЂЄWhat was that smirk about?

167
00:11:10,461 --> 00:11:12,755
вЂЄCheon Yeo-ri. Do you hate me that much?

168
00:11:12,838 --> 00:11:14,590
вЂЄAm I not good enough for your cousin?

169
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,885
вЂЄNot good enough doesn't even cover it.

170
00:11:18,886 --> 00:11:20,554
вЂЄThe truth is, Jang Eun-ju

171
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,891
вЂЄcame to our hotel before she went missing.

172
00:11:27,395 --> 00:11:28,562
вЂЄHello, ma'am.

173
00:11:29,271 --> 00:11:31,273
вЂЄI'll speak with her. Can you excuse us?

174
00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:32,274
вЂЄYes, of course.

175
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:40,491
вЂЄYou want to reserve Siena Hall?

176
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:42,076
вЂЄYes.

177
00:11:42,159 --> 00:11:46,038
вЂЄIs there a problem
вЂЄfor you to come see me in person?

178
00:11:46,122 --> 00:11:47,873
вЂЄNo, there's no problem.

179
00:11:48,374 --> 00:11:51,252
вЂЄIt's just that the name of your groom

180
00:11:52,002 --> 00:11:54,004
вЂЄmade me wonder if it's the person

181
00:11:54,797 --> 00:11:56,048
вЂЄI happen to know.

182
00:11:58,300 --> 00:11:59,677
вЂЄYes, it's him.

183
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:04,306
вЂЄYou see, there's nothing else I can do,

184
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:06,058
вЂЄso I had no choice but to come here.

185
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:12,022
вЂЄHe asked me to marry him
вЂЄand put this ring on my finger,

186
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:15,568
вЂЄbut then he broke up with me
вЂЄand started dating someone else.

187
00:12:20,448 --> 00:12:21,824
вЂЄI'm pregnant.

188
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:27,288
вЂЄI can't live without Seung-jae.

189
00:12:29,123 --> 00:12:30,583
вЂЄWill you please help me?

190
00:12:39,049 --> 00:12:40,551
вЂЄWhat stupid crap is this?

191
00:12:41,051 --> 00:12:43,179
вЂЄYou think she got pregnant
вЂЄjust from holding hands?

192
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:46,056
вЂЄ-You're saying it wasn't you?
вЂЄ-Of course not!

193
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:48,309
вЂЄShe's a professional
вЂЄwhen it comes to bluffing and lying.

194
00:12:48,934 --> 00:12:50,686
вЂЄYou don't believe what she said, do you?

195
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:53,647
вЂЄI guess the only way to find out

196
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:55,232
вЂЄis to set up a three-way encounter.

197
00:12:55,816 --> 00:12:56,734
вЂЄA three-way encounter?

198
00:12:57,401 --> 00:12:58,903
вЂЄYou, me, and who else?

199
00:12:59,403 --> 00:13:00,237
вЂЄJang Eun-ju.

200
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:05,784
вЂЄJust how would you sit
вЂЄface-to-face with the dead?

201
00:13:05,868 --> 00:13:08,954
вЂЄYou said she wasn't dead, but in hiding.

202
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:10,998
вЂЄWasn't that the story you told?

203
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:15,377
вЂЄWell, yes. She disappeared.

204
00:13:16,337 --> 00:13:17,713
вЂЄIf something feels off,

205
00:13:17,796 --> 00:13:20,466
вЂЄisn't it best to cover all bases?

206
00:13:20,549 --> 00:13:22,259
вЂЄLet's go for a three-way encounter.

207
00:13:32,186 --> 00:13:35,731
вЂЄSo you're saying
вЂЄJang Eun-ju is coming here?

208
00:13:38,817 --> 00:13:39,902
вЂЄShe could be here already.

209
00:13:42,613 --> 00:13:43,781
вЂЄCome on in.

210
