вЂЄwill fight hard for the equity.

414
00:29:00,530 --> 00:29:02,198
вЂЄYes, I'll be more careful.

415
00:29:03,450 --> 00:29:07,078
вЂЄThe PR Team will release a statement
вЂЄon Ha-ri's engagement.

416
00:29:08,163 --> 00:29:10,957
вЂЄShe's already upset as it is,
вЂЄso don't do anything to provoke her.

417
00:29:15,628 --> 00:29:18,548
вЂЄAs for the CL Raymond Hotel business
вЂЄI mentioned last time,

418
00:29:18,631 --> 00:29:21,968
вЂЄat least get in touch with them
вЂЄbefore rejecting it outright.

419
00:29:23,178 --> 00:29:26,514
вЂЄYou didn't bring it up again,
вЂЄso I thought that matter was closed.

420
00:29:26,598 --> 00:29:27,599
вЂЄActuallyвЂ¦

421
00:29:28,641 --> 00:29:29,517
вЂЄWellвЂ¦

422
00:29:30,852 --> 00:29:32,979
вЂЄTheir CEO approached me with an offer.

423
00:29:34,355 --> 00:29:36,024
вЂЄHe seems quite eager too.

424
00:29:36,107 --> 00:29:38,443
вЂЄWhy don't you hear what he has to say?

425
00:29:41,946 --> 00:29:44,073
вЂЄCORRECTIONAL SERVICES
вЂЄADVANCING ORDER AND HUMAN RIGHTS

426
00:29:44,157 --> 00:29:46,326
вЂЄHe wants me to lie low?

427
00:29:46,868 --> 00:29:48,077
вЂЄHe won't help me out then?

428
00:29:48,161 --> 00:29:50,538
вЂЄThat's the best we can do for now.

429
00:29:51,122 --> 00:29:52,874
вЂЄSo this is what my dad's like.

430
00:29:52,957 --> 00:29:55,376
вЂЄHe milked me for all I'm worth
вЂЄwith the arranged marriage,

431
00:29:55,460 --> 00:29:57,629
вЂЄbut now that he's at a loss,
вЂЄhe'll cut ties with me?

432
00:29:57,712 --> 00:29:59,464
вЂЄI've done as he said,

433
00:30:00,507 --> 00:30:03,885
вЂЄand now he thinks I'm some livestock
вЂЄthat he grazes, doesn't he?

434
00:30:03,968 --> 00:30:04,803
вЂЄPardon?

435
00:30:04,886 --> 00:30:06,763
вЂЄGive my dad a message.

436
00:30:07,347 --> 00:30:09,349
вЂЄThe cub of a tiger is still a tiger,

437
00:30:09,933 --> 00:30:12,435
вЂЄnot some livestock that crawls on command.

438
00:30:12,519 --> 00:30:15,063
вЂЄDon't say that.
вЂЄThe assemblyman cares a lot about--

439
00:30:15,146 --> 00:30:16,231
вЂЄCome on.

440
00:30:16,314 --> 00:30:18,775
вЂЄYou're his lawyer,
вЂЄso you know what my dad has been up to.

441
00:30:18,858 --> 00:30:22,445
вЂЄIllegal favors, bribery,
вЂЄeven trading shares in borrowed names.

442
00:30:22,529 --> 00:30:26,032
вЂЄGetting a freeway to curve
вЂЄright through his land was a work of art.

443
00:30:27,450 --> 00:30:29,285
вЂЄI saved every bit of evidence

444
00:30:30,119 --> 00:30:32,664
вЂЄof his deeds onto a flash drive.

445
00:30:37,585 --> 00:30:38,628
вЂЄPass him a message.

446
00:30:39,295 --> 00:30:40,964
вЂЄTell him I'll see what his next move is

447
00:30:41,881 --> 00:30:43,383
вЂЄbefore I decide what mine will be.

448
00:30:45,969 --> 00:30:48,555
<i>вЂЄAccording to medical records,</i>
<i>вЂЄthe late Jang Eun-ju</i>

449
00:30:49,180 --> 00:30:52,600
<i>вЂЄhad psychological issues</i>
<i>вЂЄincluding symptoms of delusion.</i>

450
00:30:52,684 --> 00:30:55,019
вЂЄEMERGENCY PRESS CONFERENCE:
вЂЄASSEMBLYMAN PARK, PARK SEUNG-JAE'S FATHER

451
00:30:55,103 --> 00:30:57,772
<i>вЂЄThe deceased falsified her background,</i>

452
00:30:57,856 --> 00:31:00,608
<i>вЂЄeducation, and work experience,</i>
<i>вЂЄpractically everything.</i>

453
00:31:01,234 --> 00:31:03,987
<i>вЂЄShe approached my naive son</i>
<i>вЂЄwith an ulterior motive,</i>

454
00:31:04,654 --> 00:31:07,407
<i>вЂЄand spread groundless rumors</i>
<i>вЂЄto tarnish his reputation.</i>

455
00:31:07,991 --> 00:31:10,618
<i>вЂЄNot only did she use them for blackmail,</i>

456
00:31:11,119 --> 00:31:13,204
<i>вЂЄ-she took large sums of moneyвЂ¦</i>
вЂЄ-We found her body

457
00:31:13,288 --> 00:31:14,789
вЂЄand found clear evidence of her murder.

458
00:31:15,498 --> 00:31:17,792
вЂЄThis is how the powerful
вЂЄuse the media to change the narrative.

459
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:20,253
вЂЄAt the rate of how this is going,

460
00:31:20,336 --> 00:31:22,130
вЂЄthe appeal might not go as planned.

461
00:31:22,213 --> 00:31:24,215
вЂЄHe's digging up the victim's past

462
00:31:24,299 --> 00:31:26,885
вЂЄto tarnish her character
вЂЄand change the public's mind.

463
00:31:32,557 --> 00:31:35,101
вЂЄI have to say, he's a pretty great actor.

464
00:31:35,184 --> 00:31:38,605
вЂЄLet's see how powerful your dad is.
вЂЄI won't just sit around myself.

465
00:31:48,865 --> 00:31:50,116
вЂЄHey, Park.

466
00:31:50,199 --> 00:31:52,660
вЂЄYou never called
вЂЄsince you got transferred to Jeju Island.

467
00:31:52,744 --> 00:31:54,162
<i>вЂЄI have been in touch.</i>

468
00:31:54,245 --> 00:31:57,498
<i>вЂЄMy wedding's this weekend</i>
<i>вЂЄand only you haven't RSVPed yet.</i>

469
00:31:57,582 --> 00:31:59,876
<i>вЂЄ-What kind of friend are you?</i>
вЂЄ-A wedding?

470
00:31:59,959 --> 00:32:00,793
вЂЄWhat wedding?

471
00:32:00,877 --> 00:32:03,463
<i>вЂЄI sent an invite ages ago.</i>
<i>вЂЄYou didn't even pick up my calls.</i>

472
00:32:03,546 --> 00:32:05,423
вЂЄOh, my bad. I'll check right away.

473
00:32:06,966 --> 00:32:08,259
вЂЄPARK DO-JUN & YOO HYE-WON,
вЂЄSATURDAY, FEBRUARY 7, 2026

474
00:32:09,802 --> 00:32:11,638
вЂЄCL RAYMOND HOTEL
вЂЄ3RD FLOOR, FORГЉT NOIRE BALLROOM

475
00:32:13,222 --> 00:32:14,933
вЂЄWhat even is life?

476
00:32:15,016 --> 00:32:16,851
вЂЄI almost missed my best friend's wedding.

477
00:32:17,644 --> 00:32:19,479
вЂЄ-It's in Jeju Island?
вЂЄ-Yes.

478
00:32:19,562 --> 00:32:21,481
вЂЄGood for you.
вЂЄTreat it like a special holiday.

479
00:32:21,564 --> 00:32:24,025
вЂЄIf you're going to Jeju,
вЂЄyou should try Grandma Chun-hui's.

480
00:32:24,817 --> 00:32:26,945
вЂЄGo and try the abalone, steamed conch,

481
00:32:27,028 --> 00:32:29,113
вЂЄsea urchin roe, and fresh sea squirts.

482
00:32:29,197 --> 00:32:31,032
вЂЄEat all you can and even more for me.

483
00:33:12,365 --> 00:33:13,324
вЂЄHello, ma'am.

484
00:33:15,118 --> 00:33:16,327
вЂЄThis way, please.

485
00:33:32,844 --> 00:33:34,679
вЂЄHOUSE OF HAENA
вЂЄA HAENYEO'S DREAM TAKES FLIGHT

486
00:33:59,495 --> 00:34:02,123
вЂЄAUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

487
00:34:11,090 --> 00:34:12,050
вЂЄHello.

488
00:34:12,133 --> 00:34:15,595
вЂЄYour recent New York collection
вЂЄwas a great success.

489
00:34:15,678 --> 00:34:19,640
вЂЄThe dress you collaborated on
вЂЄwith celebrity Heidi Markle

490
00:34:19,724 --> 00:34:21,267
вЂЄwas especially a massive hit.

491
00:34:21,350 --> 00:34:24,479
вЂЄYes, it was inspired by
вЂЄKorean folk paintings.

492
00:34:24,562 --> 00:34:27,899
вЂЄIt's a perfect mix of Asian sensibilities
вЂЄand modern values,

493
00:34:27,982 --> 00:34:31,277
вЂЄand it represents everything
вЂЄthat I'm known for.

494
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:35,239
вЂЄCould you give us a bit more info
вЂЄon the concept of this show?

495
00:34:37,450 --> 00:34:38,618
вЂЄYes, about that.

496
00:34:38,701 --> 00:34:41,162
вЂЄWhy don't you
вЂЄsee it for yourself at the show?

497
00:34:41,245 --> 00:34:43,664
вЂЄYou'll write lots of nice things
вЂЄabout it, right?

498
00:34:46,709 --> 00:34:49,504
вЂЄThank you. Hae-na Jung is incredibly busy.

499
00:34:49,587 --> 00:34:51,672
вЂЄShall we head to the show venue now?

500
00:34:53,674 --> 00:34:55,093
вЂЄThank you for coming.

501
00:34:55,176 --> 00:34:56,803
вЂЄEnjoy the meal as well.

502
00:34:58,471 --> 00:34:59,806
вЂЄHey, Do-jun.

503
00:34:59,889 --> 00:35:01,891
вЂЄ-Gang-uk, you made it.
вЂЄ-Hey, man.

504
00:35:01,974 --> 00:35:03,184
вЂЄYou got here on time.

505
00:35:03,267 --> 00:35:05,686
вЂЄI'm sorry, work has been crazy lately.

506
00:35:05,770 --> 00:35:07,480
вЂЄYou should take it slow, you know.

507
00:35:07,563 --> 00:35:09,023
вЂЄ-Congratulations.
вЂЄ-Hello, thank you.

508
00:35:10,274 --> 00:35:11,567
вЂЄYou can let go now.

509
00:35:11,651 --> 00:35:13,236
вЂЄYeah, sorry. I'm just nervous.

510
00:35:14,529 --> 00:35:16,572
вЂЄWhy don't you spend the night
вЂЄwhile you're here?

511
00:35:16,656 --> 00:35:18,241
вЂЄI can't. I have to get back.

512
00:35:18,324 --> 00:35:21,244
вЂЄI got a free night at a suite here
вЂЄin the wedding package.

513
00:35:21,327 --> 00:35:23,121
вЂЄI can't use it
вЂЄbecause I'm leaving for my honeymoon.

514
00:35:23,204 --> 00:35:25,706
вЂЄ-Just take the room.
вЂЄ-No way. That's too much.

515
00:35:26,207 --> 00:35:28,459
вЂЄ-Mr. Park?
вЂЄ-Yes. I'm coming.

516
00:35:28,543 --> 00:35:30,044
вЂЄ-The room is yours, okay?
вЂЄ-Hey.

517
00:35:30,128 --> 00:35:32,296
вЂЄ-I put it in your name.
вЂЄ-Hey, Do-jun.

518
00:35:32,380 --> 00:35:33,256
вЂЄSpend the night.

519
00:35:33,339 --> 00:35:34,674
вЂЄCongratulations, Do-jun!

520
00:35:35,883 --> 00:35:37,343
вЂЄThat punk.

521
00:35:41,055 --> 00:35:42,723
вЂЄPlease wait a moment.

522
00:35:51,399 --> 00:35:52,316
вЂЄShe's here.

523
00:36:15,923 --> 00:36:16,883
вЂЄKang Min-hwan?

524
00:36:18,467 --> 00:36:21,137
вЂЄ-It's been a really long time.
вЂЄ-You recognized me.

525
00:36:21,888 --> 00:36:23,973
вЂЄI was worried you wouldn't.

526
00:36:25,224 --> 00:36:27,310
вЂЄYou're the one
вЂЄmy grandma wanted me to meet?

527
00:36:28,269 --> 00:36:30,354
вЂЄYes. I contacted her.

528
00:36:34,108 --> 00:36:35,359
вЂЄCome on.

529
00:36:35,443 --> 00:36:37,528
вЂЄFriends don't have to shake hands.

530
00:36:38,529 --> 00:36:39,822
вЂЄWhen did you come back to Korea?

531
00:36:39,906 --> 00:36:40,907
вЂЄLast year.

532
00:36:42,617 --> 00:36:44,410
вЂЄI was pretty busy getting things on track.

533
00:36:45,119 --> 00:36:46,037
вЂЄI'm not surprised.

534
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:47,121
вЂЄHow are you doing?

535
00:36:48,039 --> 00:36:49,332
вЂЄI wanted to reach out to you sooner,

536
00:36:49,999 --> 00:36:50,833
вЂЄbut I was worried

537
00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:53,544
вЂЄthat if I contacted you too oftenвЂ¦

538
00:36:54,921 --> 00:36:56,422
вЂЄI'd be reminded of Ji-hwan?

539
00:36:57,381 --> 00:36:59,675
вЂЄThat wasn't all it was,
вЂЄbut it was part of it.

540
00:37:02,428 --> 00:37:04,347
вЂЄI don't see why either of us

541
00:37:05,014 --> 00:37:06,140
вЂЄshould keep mentioning him.

542
00:37:07,350 --> 00:37:08,726
вЂЄWhat was that my grandma told me about?

543
00:37:09,310 --> 00:37:10,686
вЂЄWas it your idea?

544
00:37:11,270 --> 00:37:12,104
вЂЄYeah.

545
00:37:13,022 --> 00:37:15,942
вЂЄAs you know, our main businesses
вЂЄare leisure and resorts.

546
00:37:16,025 --> 00:37:20,154
вЂЄWe may lack in management capabilities
вЂЄwhen we first branch into hotels.

547
00:37:20,238 --> 00:37:22,281
вЂЄYou learn by gaining experience,

548
00:37:22,365 --> 00:37:24,450
вЂЄand that's how you become competitive.

549
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:26,410
вЂЄThat's true.

550
00:37:26,494 --> 00:37:28,621
вЂЄBut if we get some help
вЂЄfrom a global hotel chain,

551
00:37:28,704 --> 00:37:31,207
вЂЄwe'd become better known
вЂЄin a shorter period.

552
00:37:31,707 --> 00:37:34,418
вЂЄWe started off with a partnership,
вЂЄand we're doing pretty well so far.

553
00:37:34,502 --> 00:37:35,962
вЂЄOnce we're sure we're well-recognized

554
00:37:36,045 --> 00:37:38,506
вЂЄand that we have
вЂЄa competitive edge within the market,

555
00:37:38,589 --> 00:37:39,840
вЂЄthat's when we end the contract.

556
00:37:40,925 --> 00:37:43,135
вЂЄWhat do you think?
вЂЄIsn't it a pretty sound deal?

557
00:37:43,219 --> 00:37:45,137
вЂЄThat's the choice CL Group made.

558
00:37:46,138 --> 00:37:49,016
вЂЄI'm going to run Reina Hotel my way.

559
00:37:50,059 --> 00:37:50,977
вЂЄIt's a flat-out rejection.

560
00:37:53,729 --> 00:37:54,689
вЂЄHow about this then?

561
00:37:54,772 --> 00:37:57,358
вЂЄThink of it as visiting a friend's home

562
00:37:57,441 --> 00:37:59,068
вЂЄand spend a night at our hotel.

563
00:38:01,362 --> 00:38:02,405
вЂЄIf you head right back to Seoul,

564
00:38:03,030 --> 00:38:05,324
вЂЄyour grandmother will think
вЂЄI'm incompetent.

565
00:38:10,371 --> 00:38:11,455
вЂЄWe have a deal.

566
00:38:17,169 --> 00:38:18,337
вЂЄ"House of Haena"?

567
00:38:18,963 --> 00:38:20,047
вЂЄHae-na Jung?

568
00:38:20,131 --> 00:38:21,132
вЂЄDo you want to meet her?

569
00:38:22,925 --> 00:38:24,135
вЂЄHer designs aren't my style.

570
00:38:25,094 --> 00:38:26,637
вЂЄIsn't she the best in her field?

571
00:38:26,721 --> 00:38:28,014
вЂЄHello, sir.

572
00:38:28,597 --> 00:38:29,432
вЂЄOh, hello.

573
00:38:30,641 --> 00:38:32,435
вЂЄCan we see the dresses for the show today?

574
00:38:32,518 --> 00:38:33,853
вЂЄOh, the dresses?

575
00:38:35,062 --> 00:38:36,355
вЂЄThey're not open to the public.

576
00:38:37,231 --> 00:38:38,774
вЂЄBut for you, we can make an exception.

577
00:38:39,358 --> 00:38:40,234
вЂЄThis way, please.

578
00:38:49,368 --> 00:38:50,745
вЂЄSorry, I have to take this.

579
00:38:53,664 --> 00:38:54,707
вЂЄHello, Kang Min-hwan speaking.

580
00:38:55,833 --> 00:38:56,667
вЂЄYes.

581
00:38:58,002 --> 00:38:58,878
вЂЄOh, right.

582
00:39:10,389 --> 00:39:11,682
вЂЄYou're drawn to that one?

583
00:39:13,351 --> 00:39:14,435
вЂЄI'm Hae-na Jung.

584
00:39:15,227 --> 00:39:16,854
вЂЄYou're CEO Cheon Yeo-ri, right?

585
00:39:18,272 --> 00:39:21,067
вЂЄI wondered about you
вЂЄbecause you're rarely in the public eye.

586
00:39:21,901 --> 00:39:23,569
вЂЄSo this is what you look like.

587
00:39:26,697 --> 00:39:29,617
вЂЄThis is a mermaid-style dress
вЂЄinspired by <i>вЂЄhaenyeo,</i>вЂЄ Korean female divers.

588
00:39:30,701 --> 00:39:33,329
<i>вЂЄHaenyeo</i>вЂЄ and the Little Mermaid.

589
00:39:35,414 --> 00:39:37,124
вЂЄThat sounds a bit sad,

590
00:39:38,250 --> 00:39:39,502
вЂЄbut also nice.

591
00:39:39,585 --> 00:39:42,171
вЂЄ"Sad, but also nice."

592
00:39:43,297 --> 00:39:44,965
вЂЄWhat combination is that?

593
00:39:45,049 --> 00:39:46,634
вЂЄThe Little Mermaid was

594
00:39:47,551 --> 00:39:51,305
вЂЄa sad bride who had no choice
вЂЄbut to turn to bubbles.

595
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:55,351
вЂЄI like that it has a story.

596
00:39:57,019 --> 00:39:59,522
вЂЄIt feels different from the previous works

597
00:40:00,314 --> 00:40:01,315
вЂЄby House of Haena.

598
00:40:14,120 --> 00:40:16,455
вЂЄThe seafood here
вЂЄreally is on a different level.

599
00:40:18,791 --> 00:40:21,252
вЂЄBy the way, where's Grandma Chun-hui?

600
00:40:21,335 --> 00:40:22,962
вЂЄPil-dong told me to say hi for him.

601
00:40:23,921 --> 00:40:26,173
вЂЄShe comes in sparingly these days.

602
00:40:26,966 --> 00:40:29,969
вЂЄShe's been acting strange
вЂЄsince her granddaughter lost her job.

603
00:40:30,511 --> 00:40:31,679
вЂЄMaybe that's why.

604
00:40:31,762 --> 00:40:34,265
вЂЄShe hasn't been able to dive much either.

605
00:40:34,348 --> 00:40:36,684
вЂЄWhy talk about it when it's not good news?

606
00:40:37,726 --> 00:40:39,061
вЂЄWhy don't you join me?

607
00:40:40,771 --> 00:40:42,022
вЂЄYou eat all you want.

608
00:40:44,358 --> 00:40:45,192
вЂЄMA GANG-UK

609
00:40:46,360 --> 00:40:47,778
вЂЄWhy won't anything come up?

610
00:40:50,656 --> 00:40:51,824
вЂЄ-Excuse me.
вЂЄ-Sure.

611
00:40:53,784 --> 00:40:54,910
вЂЄYes, this is the front desk.

612
00:40:56,036 --> 00:40:56,912
вЂЄOh, yes, sir.

613
00:40:57,913 --> 00:40:59,373
вЂЄThe Royal Suite?

614
00:40:59,457 --> 00:41:00,458
вЂЄYes, sir.

615
00:41:06,589 --> 00:41:08,841
вЂЄ-Okay, I can confirm your booking.
вЂЄ-Great.

616
00:41:09,842 --> 00:41:12,344
вЂЄ-I'm sorry you had to wait.
вЂЄ-That's fine.

617
00:41:12,428 --> 00:41:13,637
вЂЄThank you.

618
00:41:18,100 --> 00:41:19,560
вЂЄYeah, I just checked in.

619
00:41:20,561 --> 00:41:22,813
вЂЄNo, I didn't run away. I'm here.

620
00:41:24,231 --> 00:41:25,941
вЂЄHey, thanks for this.

621
00:41:26,734 --> 00:41:28,819
вЂЄAll right. Enjoy your honeymoon.

622
00:41:29,445 --> 00:41:30,321
вЂЄBye.

623
00:41:36,952 --> 00:41:38,621
вЂЄAm I allowed to stay here on my own?

624
00:41:47,463 --> 00:41:50,257
вЂЄI'm sorry to bother you
вЂЄwhen I could manage on my own.

625
00:41:50,341 --> 00:41:51,175
вЂЄNot at all.

626
00:41:51,258 --> 00:41:54,845
вЂЄMr. Kang told me many times
вЂЄto provide you with the best service.

627
00:41:55,554 --> 00:41:56,889
вЂЄPlease enjoy your stay.

628
00:42:26,460 --> 00:42:27,378
вЂЄWhat was that?

629
00:42:40,307 --> 00:42:42,309
<i>вЂЄDo five-star hotels like this</i>
<i>вЂЄget broken into?</i>

630
00:42:43,185 --> 00:42:44,353
<i>вЂЄNo, wait.</i>

631
00:42:45,271 --> 00:42:47,523
<i>вЂЄMaybe five-star hotels</i>
<i>вЂЄare more likely targets.</i>

632
00:43:10,170 --> 00:43:11,505
<i>вЂЄAm I being too sensitive?</i>

633
00:43:43,120 --> 00:43:45,414
<i>вЂЄ"Seoul, Daejeon, Daegu, Busan,"</i>

634
00:43:45,497 --> 00:43:46,749
<i>вЂЄ"Gwanghwamun Love Song,"</i>

635
00:43:47,416 --> 00:43:48,334
<i>вЂЄ"Busan Vacance</i>вЂЄвЂ¦"

636
00:43:49,668 --> 00:43:51,253
вЂЄThis just isn't fair.

637
00:43:51,337 --> 00:43:53,756
вЂЄHow could they follow me
вЂЄall the way to Jeju Island?

638
00:43:54,632 --> 00:43:56,342
вЂЄOr is it a local ghost?

639
00:44:12,483 --> 00:44:13,442
вЂЄAll right.

640
00:45:24,513 --> 00:45:26,265
вЂЄIt's so exhausting.

641
00:47:05,822 --> 00:47:06,990
вЂЄWhat the hell?

642
00:47:09,493 --> 00:47:10,410
вЂЄWho are you?

643
00:47:10,494 --> 00:47:12,579
вЂЄAre you a stalker, not a prosecutor?

644
00:47:12,663 --> 00:47:14,706
вЂЄYou're the one who broke into my room!

645
00:47:14,790 --> 00:47:16,166
вЂЄWhat are you on about?

646
00:47:23,340 --> 00:47:25,175
вЂЄI'm so sorry. It was our mistake.

647
00:47:26,134 --> 00:47:27,344
вЂЄIt was all my fault.

648
00:47:28,095 --> 00:47:30,055
вЂЄWhen you checked in yesterdayвЂ¦

649
00:47:30,138 --> 00:47:31,056
вЂЄThe Royal Suite?

650
00:47:32,015 --> 00:47:33,392
<i>вЂЄThe CEO called and I justвЂ¦</i>

651
00:47:35,143 --> 00:47:36,270
вЂЄMA GANG-UK

652
00:47:37,521 --> 00:47:38,689
вЂЄI'm sorry.

653
00:47:38,772 --> 00:47:41,149
вЂЄ-I'm really sorry.
вЂЄ-It's fine.

654
00:48:10,512 --> 00:48:13,223
<i>вЂЄDid I graze him</i>
<i>вЂЄwhile moving about in bed last night?</i>

655
00:48:14,975 --> 00:48:16,226
<i>вЂЄDid we make contact?</i>

656
00:48:16,310 --> 00:48:18,937
<i>вЂЄWhat then? That would be a disaster.</i>

657
00:48:20,105 --> 00:48:21,189
<i>вЂЄShould I ask?</i>

658
00:48:23,191 --> 00:48:24,276
вЂЄExcuse me.

659
00:48:24,985 --> 00:48:27,571
вЂЄDid you and IвЂ¦

660
00:48:28,488 --> 00:48:31,033
вЂЄ-I mean, was there anything physical orвЂ¦
вЂЄ-Why?

661
00:48:31,658 --> 00:48:34,244
вЂЄAre you going to sue me
вЂЄfor coming onto you or something?

662
00:48:34,786 --> 00:48:37,205
вЂЄWhy would you put it like that?

663
00:48:37,289 --> 00:48:40,292
вЂЄI'm only asking if my hand touched you--

664
00:48:40,375 --> 00:48:42,044
вЂЄBack then, on the mountain that night.

665
00:48:42,127 --> 00:48:44,796
вЂЄYou claimed aggravated assault
вЂЄwhen I grabbed your sleeve.

666
00:48:44,880 --> 00:48:47,341
вЂЄIf I say you touched me,
вЂЄyou'll accuse me for coming onto you.

667
00:48:49,176 --> 00:48:50,510
вЂЄBesides, what do you take me for?

668
00:48:51,261 --> 00:48:54,139
вЂЄYou're not at all my type.

669
00:48:54,222 --> 00:48:55,807
вЂЄI'm asking out of concern.

670
00:48:55,891 --> 00:48:58,727
вЂЄI don't even care what your type is.

671
00:48:58,810 --> 00:48:59,645
вЂЄSure.

672
00:49:10,280 --> 00:49:12,366
вЂЄI asked out of concern for his well-being.

673
00:49:12,449 --> 00:49:14,785
вЂЄWho cares if he sees ghosts or not?

674
00:49:23,251 --> 00:49:25,504
вЂЄWatch your step when you get on.

675
00:49:34,471 --> 00:49:35,639
вЂЄOh, no!

676
00:49:47,901 --> 00:49:48,735
вЂЄWatch out!

677
00:50:07,796 --> 00:50:09,131
вЂЄMy goodness.

678
00:50:19,307 --> 00:50:20,350
вЂЄOh, gosh.

679
00:50:20,434 --> 00:50:21,351
вЂЄYeo-ri!

680
00:50:23,729 --> 00:50:24,813
вЂЄYeo-ri, are you all right?

681
00:50:24,896 --> 00:50:26,481
вЂЄOh, yes, I'm fine.

682
00:50:27,691 --> 00:50:29,484
вЂЄ-Are you hurt?
вЂЄ-I'm okay.

683
00:50:29,568 --> 00:50:30,777
вЂЄ-Do you need to see a doctor?
вЂЄ-No.

684
00:50:30,861 --> 00:50:34,072
вЂЄ-I think he needsвЂ¦
вЂЄ-Why is he taking all the credit?

685
00:50:34,156 --> 00:50:35,532
вЂЄI'm so sorry.

686
00:50:36,533 --> 00:50:39,244
вЂЄI let go of the suitcase
вЂЄto look after my son. I'm sorry.

687
00:50:39,327 --> 00:50:40,245
вЂЄIt's fine.

688
00:50:40,328 --> 00:50:41,413
вЂЄ-Were you hurt?
вЂЄ-No.

689
00:50:42,038 --> 00:50:43,165
вЂЄI'm really sorry.

690
00:50:44,040 --> 00:50:45,125
вЂЄYou must've been scared too.

691
00:50:45,208 --> 00:50:46,793
вЂЄ-Yes.
вЂЄ-It's okay now.

692
00:50:47,753 --> 00:50:48,879
вЂЄ-Thank you.
вЂЄ-Sure.

693
00:50:48,962 --> 00:50:49,921
вЂЄSay thank you before we go.

694
00:50:51,548 --> 00:50:52,841
вЂЄ-Hey--
вЂЄ-Good job.

695
00:50:55,510 --> 00:50:56,511
вЂЄGood job with what?

696
00:50:56,595 --> 00:50:58,054
вЂЄI'm thanking you.

697
00:50:58,138 --> 00:50:59,639
вЂЄYeo-ri could've been badly hurt.

698
00:51:03,727 --> 00:51:05,228
вЂЄHere's a voucher for a free stay.

699
00:51:05,312 --> 00:51:06,396
вЂЄIt's a token of my gratitude.

700
00:51:08,607 --> 00:51:10,358
вЂЄYou're going way overboard for nothing.

701
00:51:10,442 --> 00:51:13,403
вЂЄI'm not saying this
вЂЄbecause I want recognition,

702
00:51:13,487 --> 00:51:16,114
вЂЄbut I threw myself in harm's way
вЂЄfor Ms. Cheon.

703
00:51:16,198 --> 00:51:17,949
вЂЄSo why are you going overboard about it?

704
00:51:18,033 --> 00:51:19,534
вЂЄIf Yeo-ri gets hurt,

705
00:51:20,911 --> 00:51:22,621
вЂЄit's the same as me getting hurt.

706
00:51:26,917 --> 00:51:27,876
вЂЄIf you need anything,

707
00:51:28,752 --> 00:51:29,753
вЂЄcall me at any time.

708
00:51:30,337 --> 00:51:31,296
вЂЄCEO KANG MIN-HWAN

709
00:51:33,757 --> 00:51:34,758
вЂЄHey.

710
00:51:35,509 --> 00:51:37,302
вЂЄI really could've gotten hurt.

711
00:51:37,969 --> 00:51:38,970
вЂЄThank you.

712
00:51:40,430 --> 00:51:42,891
вЂЄWell, sure.
вЂЄYou don't need to thank me anymore.

713
00:51:42,974 --> 00:51:44,935
вЂЄBut I would've done the same for anyone.

714
00:51:48,313 --> 00:51:49,147
вЂЄLet's go.

715
00:51:49,731 --> 00:51:50,565
вЂЄOkay.

716
00:51:58,156 --> 00:51:59,658
вЂЄ"If Yeo-ri gets hurt,

717
00:51:59,741 --> 00:52:01,201
вЂЄit's the same as me getting hurt."

718
00:52:04,496 --> 00:52:07,874
вЂЄSir, it was a terrible mistake
вЂЄto check a guest into the wrong suite,

719
00:52:07,958 --> 00:52:09,209
вЂЄbut firing someone over it

720
00:52:09,751 --> 00:52:11,670
вЂЄis too harsh a penalty.

721
00:52:11,753 --> 00:52:14,631
вЂЄBoth I and this young man
вЂЄwill make sure it never happens again.

722
00:52:15,131 --> 00:52:16,716
вЂЄ-Please don't fire him--
вЂЄ-"Young man"?

723
00:52:18,134 --> 00:52:19,761
вЂЄHe's your subordinate.

724
00:52:20,595 --> 00:52:23,932
вЂЄA team has joint responsibility,
вЂЄso when a staff member messes up,

725
00:52:24,683 --> 00:52:26,476
вЂЄ-the superior also pays.
вЂЄ-Yes, sir.

726
00:52:27,811 --> 00:52:30,480
вЂЄThis incident made me see you
вЂЄin a different light.

727
00:52:31,314 --> 00:52:33,942
вЂЄOur company has
вЂЄa fairly high bar for promotions,

728
00:52:34,442 --> 00:52:36,695
вЂЄbut this has made me start to have doubts.

729
00:52:37,320 --> 00:52:38,905
вЂЄWhat if this wasn't a mistake,

730
00:52:39,489 --> 00:52:40,490
вЂЄbut your limit?

731
00:52:41,575 --> 00:52:45,120
вЂЄThat was the first friend I invited
вЂЄsince opening the hotel.

732
00:52:45,203 --> 00:52:46,830
вЂЄHow incompetent do you think I looked?

733
00:52:47,747 --> 00:52:50,458
вЂЄYou see, that actually hurt my pride.

734
00:52:51,585 --> 00:52:52,460
вЂЄI'm sorry, sir.

735
00:52:52,544 --> 00:52:56,506
вЂЄCould you find it within yourself
вЂЄto show some mercy and lenience?

736
00:53:01,386 --> 00:53:02,304
вЂЄLet's do this then.

737
00:53:03,471 --> 00:53:07,100
вЂЄResign from our hotel,
вЂЄand I'll find you a job at another one.

738
00:53:08,310 --> 00:53:09,603
вЂЄThe same goes for the young man.

739
00:53:14,524 --> 00:53:16,610
вЂЄI'm here to see my granddaughter.

740
00:53:16,693 --> 00:53:20,739
вЂЄShe used to work at this company,
вЂЄand she said she'd be here today.

741
00:53:20,822 --> 00:53:22,991
вЂЄ-Da-mi, where are you?
вЂЄ-Take a seat, ma'am.

742
00:53:23,074 --> 00:53:25,285
вЂЄ-We should get someone.
вЂЄ-Your grandma's here.

743
00:53:25,368 --> 00:53:26,578
вЂЄDa-mi!

744
00:53:26,661 --> 00:53:28,079
вЂЄWe need you to leave.

745
00:53:28,163 --> 00:53:30,332
вЂЄ-Da-mi, where are you?
вЂЄ-Excuse me.

746
00:53:30,415 --> 00:53:31,833
вЂЄ-WhereвЂ¦
вЂЄ-Give me a minute.

747
00:53:33,293 --> 00:53:34,836
вЂЄYou're Grandma Chun-hui, right?

748
00:53:34,920 --> 00:53:37,172
вЂЄMy goodness, aren't you Prosecutor Ma?

749
00:53:37,255 --> 00:53:38,882
вЂЄI was afraid I wouldn't get to see you.

750
00:53:39,758 --> 00:53:41,384
вЂЄWhat's the matter?

751
00:53:43,386 --> 00:53:44,429
вЂЄProsecutor Ma.

752
00:53:48,558 --> 00:53:52,520
вЂЄYou reported that your granddaughter Da-mi
вЂЄdidn't come home last night,

753
00:53:52,604 --> 00:53:54,981
вЂЄbut the police thinks
вЂЄshe ran away from home?

754
00:53:56,358 --> 00:53:58,318
вЂЄBut you remembered her saying
вЂЄbefore she left

755
00:53:58,401 --> 00:54:01,947
вЂЄthat she'd attend the fashion show
вЂЄbeing held at this hotel,

756
00:54:02,030 --> 00:54:03,907
вЂЄ-so you came to look for her?
вЂЄ-That's right.

757
00:54:04,574 --> 00:54:06,326
вЂЄShe won't answer her phone.

758
00:54:06,409 --> 00:54:09,329
вЂЄI'm dead worried
вЂЄsomething happened to her.

759
00:54:10,330 --> 00:54:13,500
вЂЄShe'd been acting strange
вЂЄthe past few days.

760
00:54:13,583 --> 00:54:16,711
вЂЄDid she say anything about meeting anyone?

761
00:54:16,795 --> 00:54:17,963
вЂЄShe only said

762
00:54:18,046 --> 00:54:21,633
вЂЄshe was going to the hotel
вЂЄto see someone's event.

763
00:54:22,509 --> 00:54:23,468
вЂЄProsecutor Ma.

764
00:54:23,551 --> 00:54:27,097
вЂЄWill you please find Da-mi for me?

765
00:54:30,600 --> 00:54:33,144
вЂЄCould I take a look around her room?

766
00:54:35,230 --> 00:54:36,272
<i>вЂЄCome on in.</i>

767
00:54:44,489 --> 00:54:45,949
вЂЄTake all the time you need.

768
00:54:46,032 --> 00:54:47,367
вЂЄI'll get you something to eat.

769
00:55:38,918 --> 00:55:41,463
вЂЄGosh, why did the car brake
вЂЄall of a sudden?

770
00:55:41,546 --> 00:55:42,839
вЂЄI'm sorry, ma'am.

771
00:55:43,965 --> 00:55:45,508
вЂЄIt's fine.

772
00:56:02,942 --> 00:56:03,985
<i>вЂЄI have a favor to ask.</i>

773
00:56:05,153 --> 00:56:07,489
вЂЄSkim through it fast. Thanks.

774
00:56:07,572 --> 00:56:10,950
вЂЄCan I see the footage
вЂЄfrom that camera too?

775
00:56:11,785 --> 00:56:12,827
вЂЄYou've been at it for an hour.

776
00:56:13,495 --> 00:56:15,163
вЂЄDidn't you say you wouldn't be long?

777
00:56:15,246 --> 00:56:18,166
вЂЄYou acted so magnanimous earlier,
вЂЄthat I could call at any time.

778
00:56:19,959 --> 00:56:21,169
вЂЄCan we go forward from here?

779
00:56:21,252 --> 00:56:22,796
вЂЄA bit more.

780
00:56:22,879 --> 00:56:23,880
вЂЄMore.

781
00:56:23,963 --> 00:56:24,964
вЂЄGo further.

782
00:56:25,965 --> 00:56:26,883
вЂЄStop!

783
00:56:27,634 --> 00:56:28,468
вЂЄRight there.

784
00:56:28,551 --> 00:56:30,095
вЂЄRewind just a bit from here.

785
00:56:30,678 --> 00:56:32,347
вЂЄJust a bit. A bit more.

786
00:56:34,808 --> 00:56:37,102
вЂЄThat's it. Now skim right ahead.

787
00:56:37,977 --> 00:56:40,105
вЂЄKeep going. Keep on going.

788
00:56:40,188 --> 00:56:41,397
вЂЄMore. A bit more.

789
00:56:42,398 --> 00:56:43,274
вЂЄA bit more.

790
00:56:44,526 --> 00:56:45,401
вЂЄRight there.

791
00:56:46,319 --> 00:56:47,654
вЂЄZoom into that shot.

792
00:56:48,655 --> 00:56:50,323
вЂЄOur cameras don't have that function.

793
00:56:50,406 --> 00:56:51,241
вЂЄThey don't?

794
00:56:51,324 --> 00:56:53,284
вЂЄThis isn't one of your offices.

795
00:56:53,952 --> 00:56:55,453
вЂЄCan you please leave now?

796
00:56:56,496 --> 00:56:57,956
вЂЄI saw all I needed. Thank you.

797
00:56:58,039 --> 00:56:58,873
вЂЄSure.

798
00:57:05,130 --> 00:57:08,633
вЂЄI located the taxi
вЂЄand emailed you the details.

799
00:57:08,716 --> 00:57:11,261
вЂЄI asked the local police
вЂЄfor assistance too.

800
00:57:11,344 --> 00:57:12,887
<i>вЂЄCan you tell me what's going on?</i>

801
00:57:12,971 --> 00:57:14,055
вЂЄAll right.

802
00:57:14,139 --> 00:57:15,974
вЂЄI'll call you back in a bit.

803
00:57:51,551 --> 00:57:53,845
вЂЄThis is where the taxi dropped her off.

804
00:57:57,307 --> 00:57:58,641
вЂЄWhat is that woman doing down there?

805
00:58:18,077 --> 00:58:19,704
вЂЄ-Excuse me?
вЂЄ-Oh, shoot.

806
00:58:22,248 --> 00:58:25,001
вЂЄLife is very precious
вЂЄif you think about it.

807
00:58:26,294 --> 00:58:27,128
вЂЄHuh?

808
00:58:28,505 --> 00:58:30,965
вЂЄWhat are you doing here this time?

809
00:58:31,591 --> 00:58:33,843
вЂЄDid you have to make me jump like that?

810
00:58:34,427 --> 00:58:36,971
вЂЄWhat are you doing here on your own,
вЂЄlooking all gloomy?

811
00:58:37,055 --> 00:58:38,389
вЂЄIt's nothing.

812
00:58:38,890 --> 00:58:40,266
вЂЄDon't mind me.

813
00:58:40,892 --> 00:58:42,018
вЂЄJust go on your way.

814
01:00:50,480 --> 01:00:52,899
вЂЄSPOOKY IN LOVE

815
01:00:53,816 --> 01:00:56,069
вЂЄI just can't seem to make sense of it.

816
01:00:56,152 --> 01:00:58,112
<i>вЂЄHow did you know where to go?</i>

817
01:00:58,196 --> 01:00:59,238
вЂЄIt wasn't a coincidence, was it?

818
01:00:59,322 --> 01:01:01,574
<i>вЂЄDo you still see ghosts or something?</i>

819
01:01:01,658 --> 01:01:03,743
<i>вЂЄYou know that when it comes to succession,</i>

820
01:01:03,826 --> 01:01:05,328
<i>вЂЄit's not just about blood.</i>

821
01:01:06,120 --> 01:01:08,039
вЂЄYou want me to step down
вЂЄwhen I indicted him?

822
01:01:08,122 --> 01:01:10,708
вЂЄI swear on my life
вЂЄthat I'll help you take over Reina.

823
01:01:10,792 --> 01:01:12,168
<i>вЂЄIf I reveal the truth about that,</i>

824
01:01:12,251 --> 01:01:14,253
вЂЄGrandma will give up the idea
вЂЄof letting you take over.

825
01:01:14,337 --> 01:01:15,880
<i>вЂЄI don't plan to wait for long.</i>

826
01:01:15,963 --> 01:01:18,049
вЂЄDispel the rumor yourself,
вЂЄwith a marriage.

827
01:01:19,509 --> 01:01:21,678
вЂЄIt's Prosecutor Ma Gang-uk.

828
01:01:21,761 --> 01:01:23,513
вЂЄ-Ms. Cheon?
вЂЄ-Who are you?

829
01:01:23,596 --> 01:01:25,306
вЂЄWe shared a bed.

830
01:01:25,390 --> 01:01:27,517
вЂЄ-They must have a thing.
вЂЄ-They're playing hard to get.

831
01:01:30,103 --> 01:01:32,063
<i>вЂЄWhy does he have my gloves?</i>

832
01:01:32,146 --> 01:01:34,023
